						               													<description>This was an expansion published in Ystari magazine, issue 1.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These cards are randomly distributed at the beginning of the game, face down. They allow players to gain special powers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players keep their cards hidden and reveal them when they are used for the first time. Thereafter, they benefit from these powers to the rest of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The characters are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Entrepreneur: Can match the current bid (for example put a 9 after a 9) at any time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Investor: Get a Metro token for the majority (and the&amp;#10;associated point). Neighborhoods with a Metro token are considered as adjacent to each other (while they still exist, of course).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Politician: Whenever you receive any -1 tokens, immediately place them back down on neighborhoods (may be different) that already have at least one token. You never take the Archaeological Site card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Architect: The same-colored neighborhoods on the edge of the city are considered adjacent. &amp;quot;Trendy Neighborhood&amp;quot; tokens are worth 4 points instead of 3.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
